# Project: Smart Infrastructure Website

## Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 15 (App Router)
- **UI Library**: React 19
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS v4
- **Language**: JavaScript + JSX (NO TypeScript — no .ts or .tsx files ever)
- **Validation**: Zod
- **Forms**: react-hook-form + @hookform/resolvers
- **Utilities**: clsx + tailwind-merge (via `@/lib/utils/cn.js`)

## Core Principles
1. **Server Components by default** — only add `"use client"` when strictly necessary
2. **Feature-based structure** — page-private code lives in `src/features/`, shared code in `src/components/`
3. **Centralized data** — ALL static arrays live in `src/lib/data/`, never inside components
4. **`@/` path aliases always** — never use relative `../` imports
5. **`server-only` guard** on every file in `src/lib/api/`
6. **No secrets in client** — never use `process.env.SECRET_*` outside `src/lib/api/` or `app/api/`
7. **JSX only** — all React components use `.jsx`, all logic files use `.js`

## File Extension Rules
| File type | Extension |
|---|---|
| React components | `.jsx` |
| Logic, utils, data, config, hooks | `.js` |
| Styles | `.css` |
| Next.js config | `.js` |
| Path alias config | `jsconfig.json` |

Never create `.ts` or `.tsx` files.
